{"type":"text","timestamp":1775851085070,"sessionID":"ses_287070c89ffe3khl0ITOaSaTIo","part":{"id":"prt_d78f916f10018BAIfvmY2CH4gn","messageID":"msg_d78f908e6001iEVQTcIJxdGwh8","sessionID":"ses_287070c89ffe3khl0ITOaSaTIo","type":"text","text":"I can see this is a prompt to write a `delta-spec.md` file for the agentcube project, specifically for requirement AR-011 (Router JWT Authentication & Issuance) in Go, module `pkg/router`.\n\nBased on the specification, I need to create a delta-spec.md file with GIVEN/WHEN/THEN scenarios using the OpenSpec format. Let me create this file:","time":{"start":1775851085068,"end":1775851085068}}}
{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1775851104543,"sessionID":"ses_287070c89ffe3khl0ITOaSaTIo","part":{"id":"prt_d78f91d0f001BaGGh5gidxPbud","messageID":"msg_d78f908e6001iEVQTcIJxdGwh8","sessionID":"ses_287070c89ffe3khl0ITOaSaTIo","type":"tool","tool":"write","callID":"toolu_5e0ce17d24a34b9a9acca85f","state":{"status":"error","input":{"filePath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-qwen3.5-plus_20260410T163217Z/delta-spec.md","content":"# AR-011: Router JWT Authentication & Issuance\n\n**Module:** `pkg/router`  \n**Language:** Go  \n**Size:** M\n\n## Summary\n\nAdd JWT authentication support to the router for securing API endpoints. The router must validate incoming JWT tokens and provide token issuance capabilities.\n\n---\n\n## Requirements\n\n### R1: JWT Token Validation\n\n**GIVEN** a request arrives at a protected endpoint  \n**WHEN** the request contains a valid JWT token in the Authorization header  \n**THEN** the request should be allowed to proceed to the handler\n\n**GIVEN** a request arrives at a protected endpoint  \n**WHEN** the request contains an invalid or expired JWT token  \n**THEN** the request should be rejected with HTTP 401 Unauthorized\n\n**GIVEN** a request arrives at a protected endpoint  \n**WHEN** the request does not contain an Authorization header  \n**THEN** the request should be rejected with HTTP 401 Unauthorized\n\n### R2: JWT Token Issuance\n\n**GIVEN** a valid authentication request to the token endpoint  \n**WHEN** credentials are verified successfully  \n**THEN** a signed JWT token should be returned with appropriate claims\n\n**GIVEN** an invalid authentication request to the token endpoint  \n**WHEN** credentials cannot be verified  \n**THEN** HTTP 401 Unauthorized should be returned with no token\n\n### R3: Token Configuration\n\n**GIVEN** the router is initialized  \n**WHEN** JWT configuration is loaded  \n**THEN** the following settings must be configurable:\n- Secret key for signing\n- Token expiration duration\n- Issuer claim\n- Audience claim\n\n### R4: Middleware Integration\n\n**GIVEN** a router instance  \n**WHEN** JWT middleware is registered  \n**THEN** it should protect specified routes while allowing bypass for public endpoints\n\n### R5: Kubernetes Client Integration\n\n**GIVEN** the router needs to validate tokens against Kubernetes resources  \n**WHEN** using the client-go from `deployment/client-go.md`  \n**THEN** it should use:\n- `Clientset` for creating API clients\n- `AgentRuntimeInterface` for AgentRuntime CRD operations\n- `CodeInterpreterInterface` for CodeInterpreter CRD operations\n- Informers for caching and watching resource changes\n\n---\n\n## Data Structures\n\n### JWTConfig\n\n```go\ntype JWTConfig struct {\n    SecretKey      string        // Signing secret\n    Expiration     time.Duration // Token validity duration\n    Issuer         string        // \"iss\" claim\n    Audience       string        // \"aud\" claim\n    RefreshEnabled bool          // Allow token refresh\n}\n```\n\n### TokenClaims\n\n```go\ntype TokenClaims struct {\n    jwt.RegisteredClaims\n    UserID   string `json:\"user_id\"`\n    Role     string `json:\"role\"`\n    TenantID string `json:\"tenant_id,omitempty\"`\n}\n```\n\n---\n\n## Interfaces\n\n### JWTAuthenticator\n\n```go\ntype JWTAuthenticator interface {\n    Validate(token string) (*TokenClaims, error)\n    Issue(claims TokenClaims) (string, error)\n    Refresh(token string) (string, error)\n}\n```\n\n### Middleware\n\n```go\nfunc JWTMiddleware(auth JWTAuthenticator, skipPaths ...string) gin.HandlerFunc\n```\n\n---\n\n## Acceptance Criteria\n\n1. Protected endpoints reject requests without valid JWT tokens\n2. Token issuance endpoint returns properly signed tokens\n3. Expired tokens are rejected\n4. Token refresh mechanism works correctly\n5. Configuration is loaded from environment or config file\n6. Integration with Kubernetes client-go for resource validation\n7. Public endpoints remain accessible without authentication\n\n---\n\n## Dependencies\n\n- `github.com/golang-jwt/jwt/v5` for JWT handling\n- `github.com/volcano-sh/agentcube/client-go` for Kubernetes API access\n- `k8s.io/client-go` v0.34.1 (via generated client)\n\n---\n\n## Files to Create/Modify\n\n| File | Action | Description |\n|------|--------|-------------|\n| `pkg/router/auth/jwt.go` | Create | JWT authentication implementation |\n| `pkg/router/auth/config.go` | Create | JWT configuration structures |\n| `pkg/router/middleware/auth.go` | Create | Gin middleware for JWT |\n| `pkg/router/handlers/token.go` | Create | Token issuance/refresh handlers |\n| `pkg/router/router.go` | Modify | Add middleware registration |\n\n---\n\n## Testing\n\n### Unit Tests\n\n- JWT token validation with valid/invalid/expired tokens\n- Token issuance with various claim configurations\n- Middleware path skipping logic\n- Config loading and validation\n\n### Integration Tests\n\n- End-to-end authentication flow\n- Kubernetes client integration\n- Token refresh cycle\n"},"error":"You must read file /home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-qwen3.5-plus_20260410T163217Z/delta-spec.md before overwriting it. Use the Read tool first","time":{"start":1775851104533,"end":1775851104540}}}}
